HEADWORD: Megatherium
<hw>Meg`a*the"ri*um</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>megatherium</ets>,
fr. Gr. <grk>me`gas</grk> great + <grk>qhri`on</grk> beast.]</ety>
<fld>(Paleon.)</fld> <def>An extinct gigantic quaternary mammal, allied
to the ant-eaters and sloths. Its remains are found in South
America.</def>⟦br⟧
